HEADWORD: Anisopleura
<hw>An`i*so*pleu"ra</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/ unequal + <?/ side.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A primary division of gastropods, including those having spiral
shells. The two sides of the body are unequally developed.</def>⟦br⟧
